course.subject: STSCI
course.course_title: Statistical Methods for the Social Sciences II

notes.note: A student cannot receive credit for this course and for SOC 3010, PSYCH 3500, ENGRD 2700, ILRST 2100, PAM 2100, AEM 2100, BTRY 3010, or AP statistics.
Prerequisite: one semester of calculus.
Prerequisites: BTRY 3010, Calculus II, or the equivalent.
Prerequisite: two semesters of statistics.

course.subject: STSCI
course.course_title: Probability Models and Inference for the Social Sciences

notes.note: Prerequisites: MATH 1110 or equivalent. FORBIDDEN OVERLAP: Students may receive credit for only one course in the following group: ILRST/ECON/STSCI 3110, BTRY/STSCI 3080, ECON 3130, and MATH 4710

A two-semester sequence on statistical methods (e.g. BTRY 3010-BTRY 3020), a course on probability and distribution theory (e.g. BTRY 3080 or Math 4710), multivariable calculus, and linear/matrix algebra.
Prerequisites: BTRY 3080 or equivalent preparation; 3 semesters of calculus.
Prerequisite: CS 1112 or equivalent, MATH 2220, STSCI 3200, STSCI 3080 or MATH 4710.
Problem solving sessions to prepare students for the first four actuarial examinations (probability, financial mathematics, statistical modeling, and risk management).
Enrollment limited to MPS (AS) students.

course.subject: STSCI
course.course_title: Statistical Methods for the Social Sciences II

notes.note: Only open to MPS Applied Statistics students.
Prerequisite: Multicalculus, linear algebra, and basic statistics. Permission of department required.
Corequisites: ORIE 6700/Math 6730 (or equivalent) and at least one course in probability, or permission of instructor.
Prerequisites: Undergraduate real analysis and probability (MATH 3110, MATH 4710). The Audit option requires permission of the Instructor.
Prerequisites: BTRY 4090 or MATH 4720 , BTRY 6020 , or equivalents.
